7.  To begin uploading your files, you have three choices:
    -   Uploading 5 files at a time in TerpConnect, *or*
        (proceed to Step 8)
    -   Using Firefox FTP *or*
        (proceed to Step 9)
    -   Saving Remotely from Komodo Edit 8
        (proceed to Step 10)

8.	In TerpConnect, you can only upload 5 files at a time. 
    Find your `pub` folder again, and from the left menu, click **upload files**. 
    Go through your local folder (on your Desktop, or My Documents, or wherever) and 
    upload all of your `.html` files and images, as well as the files from the Bootstrap download. 
    Create new folders and label them exactly, `css` `js` and `img`. 
    Sort your files. 
    <figure>
        <img class="img-responsive" src="<%- @site.prefixes.img %>/screenshots/terpconnect-8.png" />
    </figure>

9.  Once you’ve downloaded the FireFTP add-on from either the Mozilla website or Dr. Kill’s Springpad link, open Firefox. 
    Click the big, orange Firefox button in your toolbar and select **Web Developer**. FireFTP opens here.
    
    <figure>
        <img class="img-responsive" src="<%- @site.prefixes.img %>/screenshots/terpconnect-9.png" />
        <figcaption></figcaption>
    </figure>
    
    Like Komodo Edit 8, you’ll need to set up a hosting server account. 
    Re-key the same information: 
        **Account Name:** TerpConnect
        **Host (Name):** `terpconnect.umd.edu`
        **Login:** your student name and password       
        **(Connection) Security:** SFTP
        **Port:** 22
    Now go back to the FireFTP toolbar, and select **connect**. 
    You may get a message about a registry key in the cache. That’s okay. Proceed. 
    You’ll now be able to copy-paste ENTIRE FOLDERS directly onto the TerpConnect Server. Do so.
    (Remember to back up from your home screen, and paste everything in `pub`.)
    <figure>
        <img class="img-responsive" src="<%- @site.prefixes.img %>/screenshots/terpconnect-10.png" />
    </figure>
 
10.	In Komodo Edit 8, go to **File ► Save as Remote**. 
    (All this means is that you're saving your file on a server, not on your own computer space anymore.) 
    Now that your server, TerpConnect, has been set-up, select it from the drop-down menu. 
    All your folders will come up, so just select and save. 
    
    Rinse and repeat for ALL your files. 
    
    You will have to select, cut, and paste all your web files from your home folder into `pub`, as 
    `pub` doesn’t automatically appear in Komodo Edit.
    
    (If **Save as Remote** is greyed out, make sure your cursor is clicked on the code, not the preview. 
     If you don't see a folder, hit the **Refresh** icon.)
     <figure>
         <img class="img-responsive" src="<%- @site.prefixes.img %>/screenshots/terpconnect-11.png" />
         <figcaption></figcaption>
     </figure>
 
11. To test your page, open a new tab or window in your browser. 
    Type in `terpconnect.umd.edu/~name/index.html` (with `name` replace by whatever your username is). 
    
    **You should be live now!**
    
    (If your page looks really plain, double-check that all of those other files from Bootstrap were uploaded too. 
    I also found that the formatting didn't work unless I recreated the exact same setup of folders and files from the Bootstrap download. 
    So in your `pub` folder, create folders, `img`, `css`, and `js` and place your files accordingly. 
    Try again. It should work now.)
